SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 8
By Massey
A RESOLUTION to congratulate the University of Tennessee
Volunteers baseball team, 2024 NCAA Men's
College World Series champion.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should honor and
commend those extraordinary athletic teams that, through their magnificent exploits, bring honor
to the State of Tennessee and serve as exceptional ambassadors of this State; and
WHEREAS, the University of Tennessee (UT) Volunteers baseball team recently
completed one of the greatest seasons in the history of the university's baseball program, as the
team took home its first NCAA Men's College World Series championship in program history
and finished the season with a 60-13 record; and
WHEREAS, the first No. 1 national seed to win the national title since 1999, the UT
Volunteers defeated Texas A&M University 6-5 on Monday, June 25, 2024, to win the 2024
NCAA Men's College World Series, a testament to the dedication, perseverance, and work ethic
of the players, coaches, and staff of the UT Volunteers baseball program; and
WHEREAS, the 2024 UT Volunteers baseball team is the first sixty-win Southeastern
Conference baseball team in history; and
WHEREAS, the UT Volunteers baseball team set a National Collegiate Athletics
Association record with five players recording twenty or more homeruns during the 2024
season; and
WHEREAS, each member of the UT Volunteers coaching staff deserves recognition,
including Head Coach Tony Vitello, Associate Head Coach Josh Elander, Assistant Coach
Frank Anderson, Assistant Coach Richard Jackson, Director of Player Development Luke
Bonfield, and Student Assistant Coach Parker Serrano; and
